Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 of Feet MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
And I select 'Ligamenta' from the dropdown menu

When I select 'Tear of the spring ligament complex' radio button
Then 'Inferoplantar longitudinal ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Medioplantar oblique ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Superomedial calcaneonavicular ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Partial tear' radio button is enabled
And 'Complete tear' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Partial tear' radio button
Then 'Ligament thickening > 5mm' radio button is enabled
And 'Ligament thinning < 2mm' radio button is enabled
And 'Increased T2 signal' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Complete tear' radio button
Then 'With retraction' checkbox is enabled
